KEY POINTS (informational summary, not legal advice):

1. You can use, modify, and self-host Trove AI for any purpose, including
   commercial use.

2. If you modify Trove AI and:
   (a) distribute the modified binary/source, OR
   (b) operate it as a network service (e.g. SaaS) that users interact with,
   then you MUST provide the complete corresponding source code of your
   modified version to those users.

3. This includes any forks deployed on the public internet.

4. Choosing AGPL means: open contributions stay open. A company forking
   Trove AI to run as a closed-source SaaS would violate the license.

If you need different terms (e.g. proprietary closed-source SaaS deployment),
contact the maintainer for a commercial license.
